    "body": "<!--\r\n**Note:**\r\n- Do not use the bug and feature tracker for support requests. Use the `cython-users` mailing list instead.\r\n- Did you search for similar issues already? Please do, it helps to save us precious time that we otherwise could not invest into development.\r\n- Did you try the latest master branch or pre-release? It might already have what you want to report. Also see the [Changelog](https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/master/CHANGES.rst) regarding recent changes.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nIn my code we have used a local function pandas_udf inside method of a class. But when we package this code, i am\r\ngetting picking error. \r\n_pickle.PicklingError: Can't pickle <cyfunction Overfit.get_dummies.<locals>.overfit at 0x000002DF651BC528>: it's not found as tools.estimation.Overfit.Overfit.get_dummies.<locals>.overfit\r\n [...]\r\n```cython\r\n# add use case related code here\r\n    def get_dummies(self, df_sales: pd.DataFrame) -> DataFrame:\r\n\r\n        schema_str = StructType([\r\n            StructField(store_col_copy, DoubleType(), True),\r\n            StructField(yrmo_col_copy, DoubleType(), True),\r\n            StructField(sku_col_copy, DoubleType(), True),\r\n            StructField('utilities', DoubleType(), True)])\r\n\r\n        @pandas_udf(schema_str, PandasUDFType.GROUPED_MAP)\r\n        def overfit(df_sales_sample):\r\n            store = df_sales_sample[store_col_copy].iloc[0]\r\n            yrmo = df_sales_sample[yrmo_col_copy].iloc[0]\r\n\r\n            overfit_util = pd.Series({u: dummies[i] for (i, u) in enumerate(skus_sample)}).to_frame().reset_index()\r\n            overfit_util.columns = [sku_col_copy, 'overfit_utilities']\r\n            overfit_util[store_col_copy] = store\r\n            overfit_util[yrmo_col_copy] = yrmo\r\n            return overfit_util.drop_duplicates()\r\n\r\n        df_sales_spark = self._spark.createDataFrame(df_sales)\r\n        overfit_spark = df_sales_spark.groupby([store_col_copy, yrmo_col_copy]).apply(overfit)\r\n        return overfit_spark\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\nPlease add the feature so that internal function is recognized when python code is packaged using cython\r\n```cython\r\n# add a proposed code/syntax example here\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Describe alternatives you've considered**\r\nA clear and concise description of any alternative solutions or features you've considered.\r\n```cython\r\n# add alternative code/syntax proposals here\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nAdd any other context about the feature request here.\r\n",
